    "body": "> > convert test suite to ape (can use jinja to parametrize contracts)\r\n> \r\n> Is this for the entire test suite? I recall it was discussed with reference to the `examples` directory during the meeting.\r\n\r\nYes, start with `examples`, eventually port over dynamic test cases (static \"compile only\" and exception tests) don't require any of it.\r\n\r\nThe nice thing is to be able to configure the backend used for testing, so can start with eth-tester (which we use today) and switch over foundry (much faster) for that type of testing. It also let's you add other compilers, so can create compatibility tests with Solidity as well.",
