    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "> Got it. If I understood correctly, it can be broken down into the following steps/PRs (for future reference):\r\n> \r\n> 1. Convert `examples/` directory in test suite to use Ape with existing eth-tester backend.\r\n> 2. Convert dynamic test cases in rest of the test suite to use Ape with existing eth-tester backend.\r\n> 3. Switch backend from eth-tester to Foundry/Anvil.\r\n> 4. Add compatibility tests.\r\n\r\nYep, that sounds about correct. Note that I'm not sure how well the xdist support will work, ape currently does not support xdist but it shouldn't affect non-ape tests. eth-tester might even work better w/ xdist because it's all an in-memory process. For CI though, it will definitely be faster to use Foundry, it's all single-threaded anyways.",
